#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "&turtlescript; Programming Reference"
msgstr "&turtlescript; Referenca za programiranje"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the reference for &kturtle;'s &turtlescript;. In the first section "
"of this chapter have a look at some aspects of the <link linkend=\"grammar"
"\">grammar</link> of &turtlescript; programs. The second section deals "
"exclusively with <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\">mathematical "
"operators</link>, <link linkend=\"boolean-operators\">boolean (true/false) "
"operators</link> and <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparison "
"operators</link>. The third section is basically a giant list of all <link "
"linkend=\"commands\">commands</link> explaining them one-by-one. Section "
"four explains how to <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">assign</link> "
"values to <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</link>. "
"Finally we explain how to arrange the execution of commands with <link "
"linkend=\"controlling-execution\">execution controlling statements</link> in "
"section five and how to create you own commands with <link linkend=\"learn"
"\"><userinput>learn</userinput></link> in section six."
msgstr ""
"To je referenca za &kturtle;'s &turtlescript;. V prvem delu tega poglavja si "
"oglejte nekatere vidike <link linkend=\"grammar\">slovnice</link> "
"&turtlescript; programi. Drugi razdelek obravnava izključno <link linkend="
"\"mathematical-operators\">matematične operatorje</link>, <link linkend="
"\"boolean-operators\">logične (true/false) operatorje</link> in <link "
"linkend=\"comparing-operators\">operatorji primerjave</link>. Tretji "
"razdelek je v bistvu ogromen seznam vseh <link linkend=\"commands\">ukazov</"
"link>, ki jih razlaga enega za drugim. V četrtem razdelku je razloženo, kako "
"<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">dodeliti</link> vrednosti <link "
"linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">spremenljivkam</link>. Nazadnje "
"razložimo, kako urediti izvajanje ukazov s <link linkend=\"controlling-"
"execution\">stavki za nadzor izvajanja</link> v petem razdelku in kako "
"ustvariti lastne ukaze s <link linkend=\"learn\"><userinput> naučite se</"
"userinput></link> v šestem razdelku."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Grammar of &turtlescript;"
msgstr "Slovnica &turtlescript;"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:7
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As in any language, &turtlescript; has different types of words and symbols. "
"In English we distinguish verbs (like 'to walk' or 'to sing') and nouns "
"(like 'sister' or 'house'), they are used for different purposes. "
"&turtlescript; is a programming language, it is used to instruct &kturtle; "
"what to do."
msgstr ""
"Kot v vsakem jeziku, &turtlescript; ima različne vrste besed in simbolov. V "
"angleščini ločimo glagole (na primer 'hoditi' ali 'peti') in samostalnike "
"(na primer 'sestra' ali 'hiša'), ki se uporabljajo za različne namene. "
"&turtlescript; je programski jezik, uporablja se za ukazovanje &kturtle; kaj "
"storiti."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this section some of &turtlescript;'s different types of words and "
"symbols are briefly explained. We explain <link linkend=\"comment"
"\">comments</link>, <link linkend=\"command\">commands</link> and the three "
"different kinds of literals: <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"string\">strings</link> and <link linkend=\"boolean-value"
"\">boolean (true/false) values</link>."
msgstr ""
"V tem razdelku so na kratko razložene nekatere različne vrste besed in "
"simbolov &turtlescript;. Razložimo <link linkend=\"comment\">komentarje</"
"link>, <link linkend=\"command\">ukaze</link> in tri različne vrste "
"literalov: <link linkend=\"number\">števila</link> , <link linkend=\"string"
"\">nizi</link> in <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">logične (true/false) "
"vrednosti</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comments"
msgstr "Komentarji"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A program consists instructions that are executed when the program is run "
"and so called comments. Comments are not executed, &kturtle; simply ignores "
"them when executing your program. Comment are there for other programmers to "
"make them understand your program better. Everything that follows on a "
"<userinput>#</userinput> symbol is considered a comment in &turtlescript;. "
"For example this little program that does nothing: <screen>\n"
"# this little program does nothing, it is only a comment!\n"
"</screen> It is a bit useless but it explain the matter well."
msgstr ""
"Program sestavljajo navodila, ki se izvajajo, ko se program izvaja, in tako "
"imenovani komentarji. Komentarji se ne izvajajo, &kturtle; jih preprosto "
"ignorira pri izvajanju vašega programa. Komentarji so za druge programerje, "
"da bolje razumejo vaš program. Vse, kar sledi simbolu <userinput>#</"
"userinput>, se šteje za komentar v &turtlescript;. Na primer ta programček, "
"ki ne naredi ničesar: <screen>\n"
"# ta programček ne naredi ničesar, je samo komentar!\n"
"</screen> Je nekoliko neuporabno, vendar dobro razloži zadevo."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Comments get very useful when the program gets a little bit more complex. It "
"can help to give some advice to other programmers. In the following program "
"you see comments being used together with the <link linkend=\"print\">print</"
"link> command. <screen>\n"
"# this program has been made by Cies Breijs.\n"
"print \"this text will get printed on the canvas\"\n"
"# the previous line is not a comment, but the next line is:\n"
"# print \"this text will not get printed!\"\n"
"</screen> The first line describes the program. The second line is executed "
"by &kturtle; and prints <userinput>this text will get printed on the canvas</"
"userinput> on the canvas. The third line is a comment. And the forth line is "
"a comment that contains a piece of &turtlescript;, if the <userinput>#</"
"userinput> symbol would be removed on the fourth line the print statement "
"will we executed by &kturtle;. Programmers say: the print statement on the "
"fourth line is 'commented out'."
msgstr ""
"Komentarji postanejo zelo uporabni, ko program postane nekoliko bolj "
"zapleten. Pomaga lahko z nasveti drugim programerjem. V naslednjem programu "
"vidite komentarje, ki se uporabljajo skupaj z ukazom <link linkend=\"print"
"\">natisni</link>. <screen>\n"
"# ta program je izdelal Cies Breijs.\n"
"natisni \"to besedilo bo natisnjeno na platnu\"\n"
"# prejšnja vrstica ni komentar, naslednja vrstica pa je:\n"
"# print \"to besedilo ne bo natisnjeno!\"\n"
"</screen> Prva vrstica opisuje program. Drugo vrstico izvede &kturtle; in "
"natisne <userinput>to besedilo bo natisnjeno na platnu</userinput> na "
"platnu. Tretja vrstica je komentar. In četrta vrstica je komentar, ki "
"vsebuje del &turtlescript;, če bi bil simbol <userinput>#</userinput> "
"odstranjen v četrti vrstici, bo &kturtle; izvedel stavek za tiskanje. "
"Programerji pravijo: stavek za tiskanje v četrti vrstici je 'zakomentiran'."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Commented lines are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with light gray in "
"the <link linkend=\"the-editor\">code editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Komentirane vrstice so <glossterm>označene</glossterm> s svetlo sivo v <link "
"linkend=\"the-editor\">urejevalniku kode</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:23 programming-reference.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commands"
msgstr "Ukazi"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using commands you tell the turtle or &kturtle; to do something. Some "
"commands need input, some give output. <screen>\n"
"# forward is a command that needs input, in this case the number 100:\n"
"forward 100\n"
"</screen> The first line is a <link linkend=\"comment\">comment</link>. The "
"second line contains the <userinput>forward</userinput> command and the "
"<link linkend=\"number\">number</link> <userinput>100</userinput>. The "
"number is not part of command, it is considered 'input' for the command."
msgstr ""
"Z ukazi poveste želvi ali &kturtle; narediti nekaj. Nekateri ukazi "
"potrebujejo vnos, nekateri dajejo izhod. <screen>\n"
"# forward je ukaz, ki potrebuje vnos, v tem primeru številko 100:\n"
"naprej 100\n"
"</screen> Prva vrstica je <link linkend=\"comment\">komentar</link>. Druga "
"vrstica vsebuje ukaz <userinput>naprej</userinput> in <link linkend=\"number"
"\">število</link> <userinput>100</userinput>. Številka ni del ukaza, šteje "
"se za 'vhod' za ukaz."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some commands like &eg; <userinput>go</userinput> need more than one input "
"value. Multiple values have to be separated using the <userinput>,</"
"userinput> character (comma)."
msgstr ""
"Nekateri ukazi, kot je &eg; <userinput>pojdi</userinput> potrebuje več kot "
"eno vhodno vrednost. Več vrednosti je treba ločiti z znakom <userinput>,</"
"userinput> (vejico)."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For a detailed overview of all commands that &kturtle; supports go <link "
"linkend=\"commands\">here</link>. Built-in commands are "
"<glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> in dark blue."
msgstr ""
"Za podroben pregled vseh ukazov, ki jih &kturtle; podpira pojdite <link "
"linkend=\"commands\">tukaj</link>. Vgrajeni ukazi so <glossterm>označeni</"
"glossterm> s temno modro barvo."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Numbers"
msgstr "Številke"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most likely you already know quite a bit about numbers. The way numbers are "
"used in &kturtle; is not much different from spoken language, or math."
msgstr ""
"Najverjetneje že veste kar nekaj o številkah. Način uporabe števil v "
"&kturtle; se ne razlikuje veliko od govorjenega jezika ali matematike."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We have the so called natural numbers: <userinput>0</userinput>, "
"<userinput>1</userinput>, <userinput>2</userinput>, <userinput>3</"
"userinput>, <userinput>4</userinput>, <userinput>5</userinput>, &etc; The "
"negative numbers: <userinput>-1</userinput>, <userinput>-2</userinput>, "
"<userinput>-3</userinput>, &etc; And the numbers with decimals, or dot-"
"numbers, for example: <userinput>0.1</userinput>, <userinput>3.14</"
"userinput>, <userinput>33.3333</userinput>, <userinput>-5.05</userinput>, "
"<userinput>-1.0</userinput>. The <userinput>.</userinput> character (dot) is "
"used as decimal separator."
msgstr ""
"Imamo tako imenovana naravna števila: <userinput>0</userinput>, "
"<userinput>1</userinput>, <userinput>2</userinput>, <userinput>3</"
"userinput>, <userinput>4</userinput>, <userinput>5</userinput>, &etc; "
"Negativna števila: <userinput>-1</userinput>, <userinput>-2</userinput>, "
"<userinput>-3</userinput> itd. In številke z decimalkami ali pikami, na "
"primer: <userinput>0,1</userinput>, <userinput>3,14</userinput>, "
"<userinput>33,3333</userinput>, <userinput>-5,05</userinput> , "
"<userinput>-1.0</userinput>. Znak <userinput>.</userinput> (pika) se "
"uporablja kot decimalno ločilo."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Numbers can be used in <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\">mathematical "
"operators</link> and <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparison "
"operators</link>. They can also be stored in <link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\">variables</link>. Numbers are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> "
"in dark red."
msgstr ""
"Številke je mogoče uporabiti v <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators"
"\">matematičnih operatorjih</link> in <link linkend=\"comparing-operators"
"\">operatorjih za primerjavo</link>. Lahko jih shranite tudi v <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">spremenljivke</link>. Številke so "
"<glossterm>poudarjene</glossterm> s temno rdečo barvo."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strings"
msgstr "Strings"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First an example: <screen>\n"
"print \"Hello, I'm a string.\"\n"
"</screen> In this example <userinput>print</userinput> is a command where "
"<userinput>\"Hello, I'm a string.\"</userinput> is a string. Strings start "
"and end with the <userinput>\"</userinput> mark, by these marks &kturtle; "
"knows it is a string."
msgstr ""
"Najprej primer: <screen>\n"
"natisni \"Pozdravljeni, jaz sem niz.\"\n"
"</screen> V tem primeru je <userinput>print</userinput> ukaz, kjer je "
"<userinput>»Hello, I'm a string.«</userinput> niz. Nizi se začnejo in "
"končajo z oznako <userinput>\"</userinput>, po teh oznakah &kturtle; ve, da "
"gre za niz."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Strings can be put in <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</"
"link>, just like <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link>. Yet, unlike "
"numbers, strings cannot be used in <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators"
"\">mathematical operators</link> or <link linkend=\"comparing-operators"
"\">comparison operators</link>. Strings are <glossterm>highlighted</"
"glossterm> with red."
msgstr ""
"Nize lahko vstavite v <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables"
"\">spremenljivke</link>, tako kot <link linkend=\"number\">števila</link>. "
"Vendar v nasprotju s številkami nizov ni mogoče uporabiti v <link linkend="
"\"mathematical-operators\">matematičnih operaterjih</link> ali <link linkend="
"\"comparing-operators\">operatorjih za primerjavo</link>. Nizi so "
"<glossterm>poudarjeni</glossterm> z rdečo."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boolean (true/false) values"
msgstr "Boolove (true/false) vrednosti"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are only two boolean values: <userinput>true</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>true</primary></indexterm> and "
"<userinput>false</userinput><indexterm><primary>false</primary></indexterm>. "
"Sometimes they are also called: <quote><userinput>on</userinput></quote> and "
"<quote><userinput>off</userinput></quote>, <quote><userinput>yes</"
"userinput></quote> and <quote><userinput>no</userinput></quote>, "
"<quote><userinput>one</userinput></quote> and <quote><userinput>zero</"
"userinput></quote>. But in &turtlescript; we call them, always, "
"<userinput>true</userinput> and <userinput>false</userinput>. Have a look at "
"this piece of &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$a = true\n"
"</screen> If you look in the <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</"
"link> you can see that the <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables"
"\">variable</link> <userinput>$a</userinput> is set to <userinput>true</"
"userinput>, and has the boolean type."
msgstr ""
"Obstajata samo dve logični vrednosti: <userinput>true</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>true</primary></indexterm> in "
"<userinput>false</userinput><indexterm><primary>false</primary> </"
"indexterm>. Včasih se imenujejo tudi: <quote><userinput>on</userinput></"
"quote> in <quote><userinput>off</userinput></quote>, <quote><userinput>da</"
"userinput></quote> in <quote><userinput>ne</userinput></quote>, "
"<quote><userinput>ena</userinput></quote> in <quote><userinput>nič</"
"userinput></quote >. Toda v &turtlescript; vedno jih imenujemo "
"<userinput>true</userinput> in <userinput>false</userinput>. Oglejte si ta "
"del &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$a = res\n"
"</screen> Če pogledate v <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inšpektor</link>, "
"lahko vidite, da je <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">spremenljivka</"
"link> <userinput>$ a</userinput> je nastavljen na <userinput>true</"
"userinput> in ima logični tip."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Often boolean values are the result of a <link linkend=\"comparing-operators"
"\">comparison operator</link>, like in the following piece of "
"&turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$answer = 10 &gt; 3\n"
"</screen> The <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> "
"<userinput>$answer</userinput> is set to <userinput>true</userinput> because "
"<userinput>10</userinput> is larger than <userinput>3</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Pogosto so logične vrednosti rezultat <link linkend=\"comparing-operators"
"\">operatorja primerjave</link>, kot v naslednjem delu &turtlescript;: "
"<screen>\n"
"$odgovor = 10 &gt; 3\n"
"</screen> <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">spremenljivka</link> "
"<userinput>$answer</userinput> je nastavljena na <userinput>true</"
"userinput>, ker <userinput>10</userinput > je večji od <userinput>3</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Boolean values, <userinput>true</userinput> and <userinput>false</"
"userinput>, are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with dark red."
msgstr ""
"Logične vrednosti, <userinput>true</userinput> in <userinput>false</"
"userinput>, so <glossterm>označene</glossterm> s temno rdečo barvo."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mathematical, boolean and comparing operators"
msgstr "Matematični, logični in primerjalni operatorji"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The title of this section might sound very difficult, yet it is not as "
"difficult as it sound."
msgstr ""
"Naslov tega razdelka se morda sliši zelo težko, vendar ni tako težko, kot se "
"sliši."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mathematical operators"
msgstr "Matematični operatorji"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the basic math symbols known as: add (<userinput>+</userinput>), "
"subtract (<userinput>-</userinput>), multiply (<userinput>*</userinput>), "
"divide (<userinput>/</userinput>) and power (<userinput>^</userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"To so osnovni matematični simboli, znani kot: seštevanje (<userinput>+</"
"userinput>), odštevanje (<userinput>-</userinput>), množenje (<userinput>*</"
"userinput>), deljenje (<userinput> /</userinput>) in potenciranje "
"(<userinput>^</userinput>)."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here a small example of the mathematical operators you can use in "
"&turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$add      = 1 + 1\n"
"$subtract = 20 - 5\n"
"$multiply = 15 * 2\n"
"$divide   = 30 / 30\n"
"$power    = 2 ^ 2\n"
"</screen> The values resulting from the mathematical operations get <link "
"linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">assigned</link> to various <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</link>. Using the <link linkend=\"the-"
"inspector\">inspector</link> you can see the values."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj je kratek primer matematičnih operatorjev, ki jih lahko uporabite v "
"&turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$dodaj = 1 + 1\n"
"$ odštej = 20 - 5\n"
"$pomnoži = 15 * 2\n"
"$divid = 30/30\n"
"$moč = 2 ^ 2\n"
"</screen> Vrednosti, ki izhajajo iz matematičnih operacij, so <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">dodeljene</link> različnim <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">spremenljivkam</link>. Z <link linkend=\"the-"
"inspector\">inšpektorjem</link> si lahko ogledate vrednosti."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you just want a simple calculation to be done you can do something like "
"this:"
msgstr "Če želite le preprost izračun, lahko naredite nekaj takega:"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "print 2010-12"
msgstr "print 2010-12"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now an example with parentheses: <screen>\n"
"print ( ( 20 - 5 ) * 2 / 30 ) + 1\n"
"</screen> The expressions inside parentheses will be calculated first. In "
"this example, 20-5 will be calculated, then multiplied by 2, divided by 30, "
"and then 1 is added (giving 2). Parentheses can also be used in other cases."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj pa primer z oklepaji: <screen>\n"
"print ( ( 20 - 5 ) * 2 / 30 ) + 1\n"
"</screen> Najprej bodo izračunani izrazi v oklepajih. V tem primeru bo "
"izračunano 20-5, nato pomnoženo z 2, deljeno s 30 in nato dodano 1 (kar "
"pomeni 2). Oklepaji se lahko uporabljajo tudi v drugih primerih."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kturtle; also has more advanced mathematical features in the form of "
"commands. Have a look at the following commands but be aware that it "
"concerns advanced operations: <link linkend=\"round\">round</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"random\">random</link>, <link linkend=\"sqrt\">sqrt</link> , <link "
"linkend=\"pi\">pi</link>, <link linkend=\"sin\">sin</link>, <link linkend="
"\"cos\">cos</link>, <link linkend=\"tan\">tan</link>, <link linkend=\"arcsin"
"\">arcsin</link>, <link linkend=\"arccos\">arccos</link>, <link linkend="
"\"arctan\">arctan</link>."
msgstr ""
"&kturtle; ima tudi naprednejše matematične funkcije v obliki ukazov. Oglejte "
"si naslednje ukaze, vendar se zavedajte, da zadevajo napredne operacije: "
"<link linkend=\"round\">okroglo</link>, <link linkend=\"random\">naključno</"
"link>, <link linkend=\"sqrt\">sqrt</link> , <link linkend=\"pi\">pi</link>, "
"<link linkend=\"sin\">sin</link>, <link linkend=\"cos\">cos</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"tan\">tan</link>, <link linkend=\"arcsin\">arcsin</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"arccos\">arccos</link>, <link linkend=\"arctan\"> arctan</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boolean (true/false) operators"
msgstr "Logični (true/false) operatorji"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Where <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\">mathematical operators</link> "
"are mainly for <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link>, boolean operators "
"are for <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean values</link> "
"(<userinput>true</userinput> and <userinput>false</userinput>). There are "
"only three boolean operators, namely: <userinput>and</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>and</primary></indexterm>, <userinput>or</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>or</primary></indexterm>, and <userinput>not</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>not</primary></indexterm>. The following piece "
"of &turtlescript; shows how to use them: <screen>\n"
"$and_1_1 = true and true    # -> true\n"
"$and_1_0 = true and false   # -> false\n"
"$and_0_1 = false and true   # -> false\n"
"$and_0_0 = false and false  # -> false\n"
"\n"
"$or_1_1 = true or true    # -> true\n"
"$or_1_0 = true or false   # -> true\n"
"$or_0_1 = false or true   # -> true\n"
"$or_0_0 = false or false  # -> false\n"
"\n"
"$not_1 = not true   # -> false\n"
"$not_0 = not false  # -> true\n"
"</screen> Using the <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</link> you can "
"see the values, yet we also supply these results as little comments at the "
"end of the lines. <userinput>and</userinput> evaluates <userinput>true</"
"userinput> only if both sides are <userinput>true</userinput>. "
"<userinput>or</userinput> evaluates <userinput>true</userinput> if either "
"side is <userinput>true</userinput>. And <userinput>not</userinput> turns a "
"<userinput>true</userinput> into <userinput>false</userinput> and a "
"<userinput>false</userinput> into <userinput>true</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Medtem ko so <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\">matematični "
"operatorji</link> večinoma za <link linkend=\"number\">števila</link>, "
"logični operatorji za <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">logične vrednosti </"
"link> (<userinput>true</userinput> in <userinput>false</userinput>). "
"Obstajajo le trije logični operatorji, in sicer: <userinput>and</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>in</primary></indexterm>, <userinput>or</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>or</primary></indexterm> in <userinput>not</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>not</primary></indexterm>. Naslednji del "
"&turtlescript; prikazuje, kako jih uporabljati: <screen>\n"
"$and_1_1 = true and true    # -> true\n"
"$and_1_0 = true and false   # -> false\n"
"$and_0_1 = false and true   # -> false\n"
"$and_0_0 = false and false  # -> false\n"
"\n"
"$or_1_1 = true or true    # -> true\n"
"$or_1_0 = true or false   # -> true\n"
"$or_0_1 = false or true   # -> true\n"
"$or_0_0 = false or false  # -> false\n"
"\n"
"$not_1 = not true   # -> false\n"
"$not_0 = not false  # -> true\n"
"</screen> Z uporabo <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</link> si "
"lahko ogledate vrednosti, vendar te rezultate posredujemo tudi kot majhne "
"komentarje na koncu vrstic. <userinput>in</userinput> oceni <userinput>true</"
"userinput> samo, če sta obe strani <userinput>true</userinput>. "
"<userinput>ali</userinput> oceni <userinput>true</userinput>, če je katera "
"koli stran <userinput>true</userinput>. In <userinput>not</userinput> "
"spremeni <userinput>true</userinput> v <userinput>false</userinput> in "
"<userinput>false</userinput> v <userinput>true</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boolean operators are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with pink."
msgstr "Boolovi operatorji so <glossterm>označeni</glossterm> z rožnato."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some more advanced examples"
msgstr "Nekaj ​​naprednejših primerov"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider the following example with <userinput>and</userinput>: <screen>\n"
"$a = 1\n"
"$b = 5\n"
"if (($a &lt; 10) and ($b == 5)) and ($a &lt; $b) {\n"
"  print \"hello\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> In this piece of &turtlescript; the result of three <link linkend="
"\"comparing-operators\">comparing operators</link> are merged using "
"<userinput>and</userinput> operators. This means that all three have to "
"evaluate <quote>true</quote> in order for the <quote>hello</quote> to be "
"printed."
msgstr ""
"Razmislite o naslednjem primeru z <userinput>in</userinput>: <screen>\n"
"$a = 1\n"
"$b = 5\n"
"če (($a &lt; 10) in ($b == 5)) in ($a &lt; $b) {\n"
"   natisni \"zdravo\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> V tem delu &turtlescript; rezultati treh <link linkend=\"comparing-"
"operators\">operatorjev za primerjavo</link> so združeni z uporabo "
"operatorjev <userinput>in</userinput>. To pomeni, da morajo vsi trije "
"oceniti <quote>true</quote>, da se <quote>zdravo</quote> natisne."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An example with <userinput>or</userinput>: <screen>\n"
"$n = 1\n"
"if ($n &lt; 10) or ($n == 2) {\n"
"  print \"hello\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> In this piece of &turtlescript; the left side of the "
"<userinput>or</userinput> is evaluating to <quote>true</quote>, the right "
"side to <quote>false</quote>. Since one of the two sides of the "
"<userinput>or</userinput> operator is <quote>true</quote>, the "
"<userinput>or</userinput> operator evaluates <quote>true</quote>. That means "
"<quote>hello</quote> gets printed."
msgstr ""
"Primer z <userinput>ali</userinput>: <screen>\n"
"$n = 1\n"
"if ($n &lt; 10) ali ($n == 2) {\n"
"   natisni \"zdravo\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> V tem delu &turtlescript; leva stran <userinput>ali</userinput> je "
"ocenjena na <quote>true</quote>, desna stran na <quote>false</quote>. Ker je "
"ena od obeh strani operatorja <userinput>ali</userinput> <quote>true</"
"quote>, operator <userinput>ali</userinput> oceni <quote>true</quote>. To "
"pomeni, da se natisne <quote>zdravo</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"And finally an example with <userinput>not</userinput> which changes "
"<quote>true</quote> into <quote>false</quote> and <quote>false</quote> into "
"<quote>true</quote>. Have a look:"
msgstr ""
"In končno primer z <userinput>not</userinput>, ki spremeni <quote>true</"
"quote> v <quote>false</quote> in <quote>false</quote> v <quote>true</"
"quote> . Poglej:"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$n = 1\n"
"if not ($n == 3) {\n"
"  print \"hello\"\n"
"} else {\n"
"  print \"not hello ;-)\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"$n = 1\n"
"če ne ($n == 3) {\n"
" natisni \"zdravo\"\n"
"} sicer {\n"
" natisni \"ni pozdravljen ;-)\"\n"
"}"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparing operators"
msgstr "Operatorji primerjave"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider this simple comparison: <screen>\n"
"$answer = 10 &gt; 3\n"
"</screen> Here <userinput>10</userinput> is compared to <userinput>3</"
"userinput> with the <quote>greater than</quote> operator. The result of this "
"comparison, the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean value</link> "
"<userinput>true</userinput> is stored in the <link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\">variable</link> <userinput>$answer</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Razmislite o tej preprosti primerjavi: <screen>\n"
"$odgovor = 10 &gt; 3\n"
"</screen> Tu se <userinput>10</userinput> primerja z <userinput>3</"
"userinput> z operatorjem <quote>večje kot</quote>. Rezultat te primerjave, "
"<link linkend=\"boolean-value\">logična vrednost</link> <userinput>true</"
"userinput>, je shranjen v <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables"
"\">spremenljivki</link> <userinput>$answer</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link> and <link linkend=\"assignment-"
"of-variables\">variables</link> (that contain numbers) can be compared to "
"each other with comparing operators."
msgstr ""
"Vse <link linkend=\"number\">števila</link> in <link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\">spremenljivke</link> (ki vsebujejo števila) je mogoče med seboj "
"primerjati s primerjalnimi operatorji."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here are all possible comparing operators: <table> <title>Types of "
"questions</title> <tgroup cols=\"3\"> <tbody> <row> <entry><userinput>$A == "
"$B</userinput></entry> <entry>equals</entry> <entry>answer is <quote>true</"
"quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> equals <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> "
"</row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A != $B</userinput></entry> <entry>not-"
"equals</entry> <entry>answer is <quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</"
"userinput> does not equal <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> "
"<entry><userinput>$A &gt; $B</userinput></entry> <entry>greater than</entry> "
"<entry>answer is <quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is greater "
"than <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A "
"&lt; $B</userinput></entry> <entry>smaller than</entry> <entry>answer is "
"<quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is smaller than <userinput>"
"$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A &gt;= $B</"
"userinput></entry> <entry>greater than or equals</entry> <entry>answer is "
"<quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is greater than or equals "
"<userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A &lt;= "
"$B</userinput></entry> <entry>smaller than or equals</entry> <entry>answer "
"is <quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is smaller than or "
"equals <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> </tbody> </tgroup> </table> "
"Please note that <userinput>$A</userinput> and <userinput>$B</userinput> "
"have to be <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link> or <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</link> that contain numbers."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj so vsi možni primerjalni operatorji: <table> <title>Vrste vprašanj</"
"title> <tgroup cols=\"3\"> <tbody> <row> <entry><userinput>$A == $B</"
"userinput> </entry> <entry>je enako</entry> <entry>odgovor je <quote>true</"
"quote>, če je <userinput>$A</userinput> enako <userinput>$B</userinput></"
"entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A != $B</userinput></entry> <entry>ni "
"enako</entry> <entry>odgovor je <quote>true</quote> če <userinput>$A</"
"userinput> ni enako <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> "
"<entry><userinput>$A &gt; $B</userinput></entry> <entry>večji od</entry> "
"<entry>odgovor je <quote>true</quote>, če je <userinput>$A</userinput> večji "
"od <userinput>$B </userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A &lt; "
"$B</userinput></entry> <entry>manjši od</entry> <entry>odgovor je "
"<quote>true</quote>, če je <userinput>$A</userinput> manjši od <userinput>$B "
"</userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A &gt;= $B</userinput></"
"entry> <entry>večje ali enako</entry> <entry> odgovor je <quote>true</"
"quote>, če je <userinput>$A</userinput> večji ali enak <userinput>$B</"
"userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput >$A &lt;= $B</userinput></"
"entry> <entry>manjše ali enako</entry> <entry>odgovor je <quote>true</"
"quote>, če <userinput>$A</userinput> je manjše ali enako <userinput>$B</"
"userinput></entry> </row> </tbody> </tgroup> </table> Upoštevajte, da sta "
"<userinput>$A</userinput> in <userinput> $B</userinput> morajo biti <link "
"linkend=\"number\">števila</link> ali <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables"
"\">spremenljivke</link>, ki vsebujejo števila."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using commands you tell the turtle or &kturtle; to do something. Some "
"commands need input, some give output. In this section we explain all the "
"built-in commands of &kturtle;. Alternatively, using <link linkend=\"learn"
"\"><userinput>learn</userinput></link>, you can create your own commands. "
"Built-in commands we discuss here are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> "
"with dark blue."
msgstr ""
"Z ukazi poveste želvi ali &kturtle; narediti nekaj. Nekateri ukazi "
"potrebujejo vnos, nekateri dajejo izhod. V tem razdelku razložimo vse "
"vgrajene ukaze &kturtle;. Druga možnost je, da z uporabo <link linkend="
"\"learn\"><userinput>learn</userinput></link> ustvarite lastne ukaze. "
"Vgrajeni ukazi, o katerih razpravljamo tukaj, so <glossterm>poudarjeni</"
"glossterm> s temno modro barvo."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving the turtle"
msgstr "Premikanje želve"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are several commands to move the turtle over the screen."
msgstr "Obstaja več ukazov za premikanje želve po zaslonu."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>forward (fw)</term>"
msgstr "<term>forward (fw)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>forward (fw)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>forward (fw)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "forward X"
msgstr "forward X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>forward</userinput> moves the turtle forward by the amount of X "
"pixels. When the pen is down the turtle will leave a trail. "
"<userinput>forward</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>fw</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>forward</userinput> premakne želvo naprej za X slikovnih pik. Ko "
"bo peresnik spuščen, bo želva pustila sled. <userinput>naprej</userinput> je "
"mogoče skrajšati na <userinput>fw</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>backward (bw)</term>"
msgstr "<term>backward (bw)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>backward (bw)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>backward (bw)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "backward X"
msgstr "backward X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>backward</userinput> moves the turtle backward by the amount of X "
"pixels. When the pen is down the turtle will leave a trail. "
"<userinput>backward</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>bw</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>backward</userinput> premakne želvo nazaj za X slikovnih pik. Ko "
"bo peresnik spuščen, bo želva pustila sled. <userinput>backward</userinput> "
"je mogoče skrajšati na <userinput>bw</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>turnleft (tl)</term>"
msgstr "<term>turnleft (tl)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>turnleft (tl)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>turnleft (tl)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid "turnleft X"
msgstr "turnleft X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput> commands the turtle to turn an amount of X "
"degrees to the left. <userinput>turnleft</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>tl</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput> ukaže želvi, naj se obrne za X stopinj v "
"levo. <userinput>turnleft</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na <userinput>tl</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>turnright (tr)</term>"
msgstr "<term>turnright (tr)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>turnright (tr)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>turnright (tr)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "turnright X"
msgstr "turnright X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>turnright</userinput> the turtle to turn an amount of X degrees "
"to the right. <userinput>turnright</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>tr</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>turnright</userinput>ukaže želvi, da se obrne za X stopinj v "
"desno. <userinput>turnright</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na "
"<userinput>tr</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>direction (dir)</term>"
msgstr "<term>direction (dir)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>direction (dir)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>direction (dir)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "direction X"
msgstr "direction X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>direction</userinput> set the turtle's direction to an amount of "
"X degrees counting from zero, and thus is not relative to the turtle's "
"previous direction. <userinput>direction</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>dir</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>direction</userinput> nastavi smer želve na količino X stopinj, "
"šteto od nič, in tako ni relativna glede na prejšnjo smer želve. "
"<userinput>direction</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na <userinput>dir</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>getdirection</term>"
msgstr "<term>getdirection</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>getdirection</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>getdirection</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>getdirection</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>getdirection</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>getdirection</userinput> returns the turtle's direction as an "
"amount of degrees counting from zero, where zero is the direction when the "
"turtle is pointing upwards."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>getdirection</userinput> vrne smer želve kot število stopinj, "
"šteto od nič, kjer je nič smer, ko je želva obrnjena navzgor."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>center</term>"
msgstr "<term>center</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>center</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>center</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>center</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>center</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>center</userinput> moves the turtle to the center on the canvas."
msgstr "<userinput>center</userinput> premakne želvo na sredino platna."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>go</term>"
msgstr "<term>go</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>go</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>go</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "go X,Y"
msgstr "go X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>go</userinput> commands the turtle to go to a certain place on "
"the canvas. This place is X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> "
"from the left of the canvas, and Y <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</"
"glossterm> from the top of the canvas."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>go</userinput> ukaže želvi, naj gre na določeno mesto na platnu. "
"To mesto je X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pikslov</glossterm> od leve "
"strani platna in Y <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pikslov</glossterm> od vrha "
"platna."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>gox</term>"
msgstr "<term>gox</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "gox (gx)"
msgstr "gox (gx)"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "gox X"
msgstr "gox X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>gox</userinput> using this command the turtle will move to X "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> from the left of the canvas "
"whilst staying at the same height. <userinput>gox</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>gx</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>gox</userinput> s tem ukazom se bo želva premaknila za X "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pikslov</glossterm> z leve strani platna, "
"medtem ko bo ostala na isti višini. <userinput>gox</userinput> je mogoče "
"skrajšati na <userinput>gx</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>goy</term>"
msgstr "<term>goy</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "goy (gy)"
msgstr "goy (gy)"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "goy Y"
msgstr "goy Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>goy</userinput> using this command the turtle will move to Y "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> from the top of the canvas "
"whilst staying at the same distance from the left border of the canvas. "
"<userinput>goy</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>gy</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>pojdiy</userinput> s tem ukazom se bo želva premaknila za Y "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pikslov</glossterm> od vrha platna, medtem ko "
"bo ostala na enaki razdalji od leve meje platna. <userinput>pojdiy</"
"userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na <userinput>gy</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the commands <userinput>go</userinput>, <userinput>gox</userinput>, "
"<userinput>goy</userinput> and <userinput>center</userinput> the turtle will "
"not draw a line, no matter if the pen is up or down."
msgstr ""
"Z uporabo ukazov <userinput>go</userinput>, <userinput>gox</userinput>, "
"<userinput>goy</userinput> in <userinput>center</userinput> želva ne bo "
"narisala črte, ne glede na to, ali pero gor ali dol."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where is the turtle?"
msgstr "Kje je želva?"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two commands which return the position of the turtle on the screen."
msgstr "Obstajata dva ukaza, ki vrneta položaj želve na zaslonu."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>getx</term>"
msgstr "<term>getx</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>getx</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>getx</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>getx</userinput> returns the number of pixels from the left of "
"the canvas to the current position of the turtle."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>getx</userinput> vrne število slikovnih pik od leve strani platna "
"do trenutnega položaja želve."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>gety</term>"
msgstr "<term>gety</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>gety</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>gety</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>gety</userinput> returns the number of pixels from the top of the "
"canvas to the current position of the turtle."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>gety</userinput> vrne število slikovnih pik od vrha platna do "
"trenutnega položaja želve."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "The turtle has a pen"
msgstr "Želva ima pero"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The turtle has a pen that draws a line when the turtle moves. There are a "
"few commands to control the pen. In this section we explain these commands."
msgstr ""
"Želva ima pisalo, ki nariše črto, ko se želva premika. Obstaja nekaj ukazov "
"za nadzor peresa. V tem razdelku razlagamo te ukaze."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>penup (pu)</term>"
msgstr "<term>penup (pu)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>penup (pu)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>penup (pu)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "penup"
msgstr "penup"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>penup</userinput> lifts the pen from the canvas. When the pen is "
"<quote>up</quote> no line will be drawn when the turtle moves. See also "
"<userinput>pendown</userinput>. <userinput>penup</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>pu</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>penup</userinput> dvigne pero s platna. Ko je pero <quote>gor</"
"quote>, ko se želva premika, ne bo narisana črta. Glejte tudi "
"<userinput>pendown</userinput>. <userinput>penup</userinput> je mogoče "
"skrajšati na <userinput>pu</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>pendown (pd)</term>"
msgstr "<term>pendown (pd)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>pendown (pd)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>pendown (pd)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid "pendown"
msgstr "pendown"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>pendown</userinput> presses the pen down on the canvas. When the "
"pen is press <quote>down</quote> on the canvas a line will be drawn when the "
"turtle moves. See also <userinput>penup</userinput>. <userinput>pendown</"
"userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>pd</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>pendown</userinput> pritisne pero navzdol na platno. Ko pero "
"pritisnete <quote>navzdol</quote> na platnu, se ob premikanju želve nariše "
"črta. Glejte tudi <userinput>pisalo gor</userinput>. <userinput>pendown</"
"userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na <userinput>pd</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>penwidth (pw)</term>"
msgstr "<term>penwidth (pw)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>penwidth (pw)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>penwidth (pw)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid "penwidth X"
msgstr "penwidth X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> sets the width of the pen (the line width) "
"to an amount of X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>. "
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>pw</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> nastavi širino peresa (širino črte) na "
"količino X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pikslov</glossterm>. "
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na <userinput>pw</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>pencolor (pc)</term>"
msgstr "<term>pencolor (pc)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>pencolor (pc)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>pencolor (pc)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid "pencolor R,G,B"
msgstr "pencolor R,G,B"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> sets the color of the pen. "
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> takes an <glossterm linkend=\"rgb\">RGB "
"combination</glossterm> as input. <userinput>pencolor</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>pc</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> nastavi barvo pisala. <userinput>pencolor</"
"userinput> kot vhod sprejme <glossterm linkend=\"rgb\">kombinacijo RGB</"
"glossterm>.<userinput>pencolor</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na "
"<userinput>pc</userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commands to control the canvas"
msgstr "Ukazi za nadzor platna"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are several commands to control the canvas."
msgstr "Obstaja več ukazov za nadzor platna."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>canvassize (cs)</term>"
msgstr "<term>canvassize (cs)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>canvassize (cs)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>canvassize (cs)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "canvassize X,Y"
msgstr "canvassize X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the <userinput>canvassize</userinput> command you can set the size of "
"the canvas. It takes X and Y as input, where X is the new canvas width in "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>, and Y is the new height of "
"the canvas in <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>. "
"<userinput>canvassize</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>cs</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Z ukazom <term>canvascolor (cc)</term> lahko nastavite velikost platna. Kot "
"vnos vzame X in Y, kjer je X nova širina platna v <glossterm linkend=\"pixels"
"\">pikslih</glossterm>, Y pa nova višina platna v <glossterm linkend=\"pixels"
"\">piksli</glossterm>. <userinput>canvassize</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati "
"na <userinput>cs</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>canvascolor (cc)</term>"
msgstr "<term>canvascolor (cc)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>canvascolor (cc)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>canvascolor (cc)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "canvascolor R,G,B"
msgstr "canvascolor R,G,B"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> set the color of the canvas. "
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> takes an <glossterm linkend=\"rgb\">RGB "
"combination</glossterm> as input. <userinput>canvascolor</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>cc</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> nastavi barvo platna. "
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> kot vhod sprejme <glossterm linkend=\"rgb"
"\">kombinacijo RGB</glossterm>. <userinput>canvascolor</userinput> je mogoče "
"skrajšati na <userinput>cc</userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:334
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commands to clean up"
msgstr "Ukazi za čiščenje"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two commands to clean up the canvas after you have made a mess."
msgstr "Obstajata dva ukaza za čiščenje platna, potem ko ste naredili nered."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>clear (ccl)</term>"
msgstr "<term>clear (ccl)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>clear (ccl)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>clear (ccl)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid "clear"
msgstr "clear"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With <userinput>clear</userinput> you can clean all drawings from the "
"canvas. All other things remain: the position and angle of the turtle, the "
"canvascolor, the visibility of the turtle, and the canvas size."
msgstr ""
"Z <userinput>clear</userinput> lahko počistite vse risbe s platna. Ostale "
"stvari ostanejo: položaj in kot želve, barva platna, vidnost želve in "
"velikost platna."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:347
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>reset</term>"
msgstr "<term>reset</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:347
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>reset</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>reset</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>reset</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>reset</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>reset</userinput> cleans much more thoroughly than the "
"<userinput>clear</userinput> command. After a <userinput>reset</userinput> "
"command everything is like is was when you had just started &kturtle;. The "
"turtle is positioned at the middle of the screen, the canvas color is white, "
"the turtle draws a black line on the canvas and the canvassize is set to 400 "
"x 400 pixels."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>reset</userinput> očisti veliko bolj temeljito kot ukaz "
"<userinput>clear</userinput>. Po ukazu <userinput>reset</userinput> je vse "
"tako, kot je bilo, ko ste pravkar zagnali &kturtle;. Želva je postavljena na "
"sredino zaslona, barva platna je bela, želva nariše črno črto na platnu, "
"velikost platna pa je nastavljena na 400 x 400 slikovnih pik."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:355
#, no-c-format
msgid "The turtle is a sprite"
msgstr "Želva je sprite"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:356
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First a brief explanation of what sprites are: sprites are small pictures "
"that can be moved around the screen, like we often see in computer games. "
"Our turtle is also a sprite. For more info see the glossary on <glossterm "
"linkend=\"sprites\">sprites</glossterm>."
msgstr ""
"Najprej kratka razlaga, kaj so sprite: sprite so majhne slike, ki jih lahko "
"premikamo po zaslonu, kot jih pogosto vidimo v računalniških igrah. Tudi "
"naša želva je sprite. Za več informacij glejte glosar o <glossterm linkend="
"\"sprites\">sprites</glossterm>."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next you will find a full overview on all commands to work with sprites."
msgstr "Nato boste našli popoln pregled vseh ukazov za delo s spriti."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The current version of &kturtle; does not yet support the use of sprites "
"other than the turtle. With future versions you will be able to change the "
"turtle into something of your own design."
msgstr ""
"Trenutna različica &kturtle; še ne podpira uporabe duhov razen želve. S "
"prihodnjimi različicami boste želvo lahko spremenili v nekaj svojega."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:362
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>spriteshow (ss)</term>"
msgstr "<term>spriteshow (ss)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:362
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>spriteshow (ss)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>spriteshow (ss)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid "spriteshow"
msgstr "spriteshow"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>spriteshow</userinput> makes the turtle visible again after it "
"has been hidden. <userinput>spriteshow</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>ss</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>spriteshow</userinput> naredi želvo znova vidno, potem ko je bila "
"skrita. <userinput>spriteshow</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati na "
"<userinput>ss</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>spritehide (sh)</term>"
msgstr "<term>spritehide (sh)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>spritehide (sh)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>spritehide (sh)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "spritehide"
msgstr "spritehide"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>spritehide</userinput> hides the turtle. This can be used if the "
"turtle does not fit in your drawing. <userinput>spritehide</userinput> can "
"be abbreviated to <userinput>sh</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>spritehide</userinput> skrije želvo. To lahko uporabite, če želva "
"ne ustreza vaši risbi. <userinput>spritehide</userinput> je mogoče skrajšati "
"na <userinput>sh</userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can the turtle write?"
msgstr "Zna želva pisati?"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The answer is: <quote>yes</quote>. The turtle can write: it writes just "
"about everything you command it to."
msgstr ""
"Odgovor je: <quote>da</quote>. Želva zna pisati: napiše skoraj vse, kar ji "
"ukažete."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>print</term>"
msgstr "<term>print</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>print</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>print</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid "print X"
msgstr "natisni X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>print</userinput> command is used to command the turtle to "
"write something on the canvas. <userinput>print</userinput> takes numbers "
"and strings as input. You can <userinput>print</userinput> various numbers "
"and strings using the <quote>+</quote> symbol. See here a small example:"
msgstr ""
"Ukaz <userinput>print</userinput> se uporablja za ukaz želvi, naj nekaj "
"napiše na platno. <userinput>print</userinput> kot vhod sprejme številke in "
"nize. S simbolom <quote>+</quote> lahko <userinput>natisnete</userinput> "
"različne številke in nize. Tukaj si oglejte majhen primer:"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$year = 2003\n"
"$author = \"Cies\"\n"
"print $author + \" started the KTurtle project in \" + $year + \" and still "
"enjoys working on it!\""
msgstr ""
"$year = 2003\n"
"$author = \"Cies\"\n"
"print $author \" je začel projekt KTurtle v \" $year \" in še vedno uživa "
"pri delu!\""

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>fontsize</term>"
msgstr "<term>fontsize</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>fontsize</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>fontsize</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "fontsize X"
msgstr "fontsize X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>fontsize</userinput> sets the size of the font that is used by "
"<userinput>print</userinput>. <userinput>fontsize</userinput> takes one "
"input which should be a number. The size is set in <glossterm linkend="
"\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>fontsize</userinput> nastavi velikost pisave, ki jo uporablja "
"<userinput>natisni</userinput>. <userinput>fontsize</userinput> sprejme en "
"vnos, ki mora biti številka. Velikost je nastavljena v <glossterm linkend="
"\"pixels\">pikslih</glossterm>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mathematical commands"
msgstr "Matematični ukazi"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following commands are &kturtle;'s more advanced mathematical commands."
msgstr "Naslednji ukazi so naprednejši matematični ukazi &kturtle;."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>round</term>"
msgstr "<term>round</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>round</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>round</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "round(x)"
msgstr "round(x)"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>round</userinput> the given number to the nearest integer. "
"<screen>\n"
"print round(10.8)\n"
"forward 20\n"
"print round(10.3)\n"
"</screen> With this code the turtle will print the numbers 11 and 10."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>round</userinput> zaokroži dano število na najbližje celo "
"število. <screen>\n"
"print round(10.8)\n"
"forward 20\n"
"print round(10.3)\n"
"</screen> S to kodo bo želva natisnila številki 11 in 10."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:416
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>random (rnd)</term>"
msgstr "<term>random (rnd)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:416
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>random (rnd)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>random (rnd)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "random X,Y"
msgstr "naključni X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>random</userinput> is a command that takes input and gives "
"output. As input are required two numbers, the first (X) sets the minimum "
"output, the second (Y) sets the maximum. The output is a randomly chosen "
"number that is equal or greater than the minimum and equal or smaller than "
"the maximum. Here a small example: <screen>\n"
"repeat 500 {\n"
"  $x = random 1,20\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnleft 10 - $x\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Using the <userinput>random</userinput> command you can add a bit "
"of chaos to your program."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>random</userinput> je ukaz, ki sprejme vnos in poda izhod. Kot "
"vnos sta potrebni dve števili, prva (X) določa minimalni izhod, druga (Y) pa "
"maksimum. Rezultat je naključno izbrano število, ki je enako ali večje od "
"minimuma in enako ali manjše od maksimuma. Tu je majhen primer: <screen>\n"
"ponovi 500 {\n"
"   $x = naključno 1,20\n"
"   naprej $x\n"
"   zavoj levo 10 - $x\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Z ukazom <userinput>random</userinput> lahko svojemu programu "
"dodate malo kaosa."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>mod</term>"
msgstr "<term>mod</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>mod</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>mod</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid "mod X,Y"
msgstr "mod X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>mod</userinput> returns remainder of the division of first "
"number by the second number."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mod</userinput> vrne preostanek deljenja prvega števila z drugim "
"številom."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:434
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>sqrt</term>"
msgstr "<term>sqrt</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:434
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>sqrt</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>sqrt</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:435
#, no-c-format
msgid "sqrt X"
msgstr "sqrt X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>sqrt</userinput> command is sued to find the square root of a "
"number, X."
msgstr ""
"Ukaz <userinput>sqrt</userinput> se uporablja za iskanje kvadratnega korena "
"števila, X."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>pi</term>"
msgstr "<term>pi</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>pi</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>pi</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>pi</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>pi</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "This command returns the constant Pi, <userinput>3.14159</userinput>."
msgstr "Ta ukaz vrne konstanto Pi, <userinput>3,14159</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sin<indexterm><primary>sin</primary></indexterm>, "
"cos<indexterm><primary>cos</primary></indexterm>, tan"
msgstr ""
"sin<indexterm><primary>sin</primary></indexterm>, "
"cos<indexterm><primary>cos</primary></indexterm>, tan"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>tan</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>tan</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sin X\n"
"cos X\n"
"tan X"
msgstr ""
"sin X\n"
"cos X\n"
"tan X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These three commands represent the world famous trigoniometrical functions "
"<userinput>sin</userinput>, <userinput>cos</userinput> and <userinput>tan</"
"userinput>. The input argument of these commands, X, is a <link linkend="
"\"number\">number</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ti trije ukazi predstavljajo svetovno znane trigonometrične funkcije "
"<userinput>sin</userinput>, <userinput>cos</userinput> in <userinput>tan</"
"userinput>. Vhodni argument teh ukazov, X, je <link linkend=\"number"
"\">število</link>."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"arcsin<indexterm><primary>arcsin</primary></indexterm>, "
"arccos<indexterm><primary>arccos</primary></indexterm>, arctan"
msgstr ""
"arcsin<indexterm><primary>arcsin</primary></indexterm>, "
"arccos<indexterm><primary>arccos</primary></indexterm>, arctan"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:473
#, no-c-format
msgid "arctan"
msgstr "arctan"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"arcsin X\n"
"arccos X\n"
"arctan X"
msgstr ""
"arcsin X\n"
"arccos X\n"
"arctan X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These commands are the inverse functions of <link linkend=\"sin\">sin</"
"link>, <link linkend=\"cos\">cos</link> and <link linkend=\"tan\">tan</"
"link>. The input argument of these commands, X, is a <link linkend=\"number"
"\">number</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ti ukazi so inverzne funkcije <link linkend=\"sin\">sin</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"cos\">cos</link> in <link linkend=\"tan\">tan</link>. Vhodni "
"argument teh ukazov, X, je <link linkend=\"number\">število</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "Input and feedback through dialogs"
msgstr "Vnos in povratne informacije prek pogovornih oken"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A dialog is a small pop-up window that provides some feedback or asks for "
"some input. &kturtle; has two commands for dialogs, namely: "
"<userinput>message</userinput> and <userinput>ask</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Pogovorno okno je majhno pojavno okno, ki ponuja povratne informacije ali "
"zahteva nekaj vnosa. &kturtle; ima dva ukaza za pogovorna okna, in sicer: "
"<userinput>sporočilo</userinput> in <userinput>vprašaj</userinput>"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>message</term>"
msgstr "<term>message</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>message</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>message</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid "message X"
msgstr "message X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>message</userinput> command takes a <link linkend=\"string"
"\">string</link> as input. It shows a pop-up dialog containing the text from "
"the <link linkend=\"string\">string</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ukaz <userinput>message</userinput> kot vhod sprejme <link linkend=\"string"
"\">niz</link>. Prikazuje pojavno pogovorno okno, ki vsebuje besedilo iz "
"<link linkend=\"string\">niza</link>."

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"message \"Cies started KTurtle in 2003 and still enjoys working on it!\""
msgstr ""
"sporočilo \"Cies je začel KTurtle leta 2003 in še vedno uživa pri delu!\""

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>ask</term>"
msgstr "<term>ask</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>ask</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>ask</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:498
#, no-c-format
msgid "ask X"
msgstr "vprašaj X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:498
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>ask</userinput> takes a <link linkend=\"string\">string</link> as "
"input. It shows this string in a pop-up dialog (similar to <link linkend="
"\"message\">message</link>), along with an input field. After the user has "
"entered a <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> or a <link linkend=\"string"
"\">string</link> into this, the result can be stored in a <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> or passed as an argument to a "
"<link linkend=\"commands\">command</link>. For example: <screen>\n"
"$in = ask \"What is your year of birth?\"\n"
"$out = 2003 - $in\n"
"print \"In 2003 you were \" + $out + \" years old at some point.\"\n"
"</screen> If the user cancels the input dialog, or does not enter anything "
"at all, the <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> is "
"empty."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>vprašaj</userinput> kot vhod sprejme <link linkend=\"string"
"\">niz</link>. Ta niz prikaže v pojavnem pogovornem oknu (podobnem <link "
"linkend=\"message\">sporočilo</link>) skupaj z vnosnim poljem. Ko uporabnik "
"vanj vnese <link linkend=\"number\">število</link> ali <link linkend=\"string"
"\">niz</link>, se lahko rezultat shrani v <link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\">spremenljivka</link> ali posredovana kot argument <link linkend="
"\"commands\">ukaz</link>. Na primer: <screen>\n"
"$in = vprašaj \"Katero je tvoje leto rojstva?\"\n"
"$out = 2003 - $in\n"
"print \"Leta 2003 ste bili na neki točki stari \" + $out + \" let.\"\n"
"</screen> Če uporabnik prekliče pogovorno okno za vnos ali sploh ne vnese "
"ničesar, je <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">spremenljivka</link> "
"prazna."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assignment of variables"
msgstr "Dodelitev spremenljivk"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First we have a look at variables, then we look at assigning values to those "
"variables."
msgstr ""
"Najprej si ogledamo spremenljivke, nato pa si ogledamo dodeljevanje "
"vrednosti tem spremenljivkam."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:516
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Variables are words that start with a <quote>$</quote>, in the <link linkend="
"\"the-editor\">editor</link> they are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> "
"with purple."
msgstr ""
"Spremenljivke so besede, ki se začnejo z <quote>$</quote>, v <link linkend="
"\"the-editor\">urejevalniku</link> so <glossterm>označene</glossterm> z "
"vijolično."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:518
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Variables can contain any <link linkend=\"number\">number</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"string\">string</link> or <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean "
"(true/false) value</link>. Using the assignment, <userinput>=</userinput>, a "
"variable is given its content. It will keep that content until the program "
"finishes executing or until the variable is reassigned to something else."
msgstr ""
"Spremenljivke lahko vsebujejo poljubno <link linkend=\"number\">število</"
"link>, <link linkend=\"string\">niz</link> ali <link linkend=\"boolean-value"
"\">logično (true/false) vrednost</link>. Z dodelitvijo <userinput>=</"
"userinput> spremenljivka dobi svojo vsebino. To vsebino bo hranil, dokler se "
"program ne konča z izvajanjem ali dokler spremenljivka ni dodeljena nečemu "
"drugemu."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:520
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use variables, once assigned, just as if they are their content. For "
"instance in the following piece of &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$x = 10\n"
"$x = $x / 3\n"
"print $x\n"
"</screen> First the variable <userinput>$x</userinput> is assigned to "
"<userinput>10</userinput>. Then <userinput>$x</userinput> is reassigned to "
"itself divided by <userinput>3</userinput> &mdash; this effectively means "
"<userinput>$x</userinput> is reassigned to product of <userinput>10 / 3</"
"userinput>. Finally <userinput>$x</userinput> is printed. In line two and "
"three you see that <userinput>$x</userinput> is used as if it is its "
"contents."
msgstr ""
"Spremenljivke, ko so enkrat dodeljene, lahko uporabite, kot da bi bile "
"njihova vsebina. Na primer v naslednjem delu &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$x = 10\n"
"$x = $x / 3\n"
"natisni $x\n"
"</screen> Najprej je spremenljivka <userinput>$x</userinput> dodeljena "
"<userinput>10</userinput>. Nato je <userinput>$x</userinput> znova dodeljen "
"sam sebi deljeno z <userinput>3</userinput> &mdash; to dejansko pomeni, da "
"je <userinput>$x</userinput> ponovno dodeljen produktu <userinput>10 / 3</"
"userinput>. Končno se natisne <userinput>$x</userinput>. V drugi in tretji "
"vrstici vidite, da je <userinput>$x</userinput> uporabljen, kot da je "
"njegova vsebina."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Variables have to be assigned in order to be used. For example: <screen>\n"
"print $n\n"
"</screen> Will result in an error message."
msgstr ""
"Spremenljivke morajo biti dodeljene, da se lahko uporabijo. Na primer: "
"<screen>\n"
"natisni $n\n"
"</screen> Prikaže se sporočilo o napaki."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please consider the following piece of &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$a = 2004\n"
"$b = 25\n"
"\n"
"# the next command prints \"2029\"\n"
"print $a + $b\n"
"backward 30\n"
"# the next command prints \"2004 plus 25 equals 2029\"\n"
"print $a + \" plus \" + $b + \" equals \" + ($a + $b)\n"
"</screen> In the first two lines the variables <userinput>$a</userinput> and "
"<userinput>$b</userinput> are set to 2004 and 25. Then in two "
"<userinput>print</userinput> commands with a <userinput>backward 30</"
"userinput> in between are executed. The comments before the "
"<userinput>print</userinput> commands explain what they are doing. The "
"command <userinput>backward 30</userinput> is there to make sure every "
"output is on a new line. As you see variables can be used just as if their "
"where what they contain, you can use them with any kind of <link linkend="
"\"operators\">operators</link> or give them as input when invoking <link "
"linkend=\"commands\">commands</link>."
msgstr ""
"Prosimo, upoštevajte naslednji del &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$a = 2004\n"
"$b = 25\n"
"\n"
"# naslednji ukaz natisne \"2029\"\n"
"print $a + $b\n"
"backward 30\n"
"# naslednji ukaz natisne \"2004 plus 25 je enako 2029\"\n"
"print $a + \" plus \" + $b + \" je enako \" + ($a + $b)\n"
"</screen> V prvih dveh vrsticah sta spremenljivki <userinput>$a</userinput> "
"in <userinput>$b</userinput> nastavljeni na 2004 in 25. Nato v dveh ukazih "
"<userinput>print</userinput> z vmes se izvede <userinput>backward 30</"
"userinput>. Komentarji pred ukazi <userinput>natisni</userinput> "
"pojasnjujejo, kaj počnejo. Ukaz <userinput>backward 30</userinput> poskrbi, "
"da je vsak izhod v novi vrstici. Kot vidite, je spremenljivke mogoče "
"uporabiti tako, kot če bi bile tam, kar vsebujejo, lahko jih uporabite s "
"poljubnimi vrstami <link linkend=\"operators\">operatorjev</link> ali jih "
"podate kot vnos pri klicanju <link linkend=\"commands\">ukazi</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One more example: <screen>\n"
"$name = ask \"What is your name?\"\n"
"print \"Hi \" + $name + \"! Good luck while learning the art of "
"programming...\"\n"
"</screen> Pretty straight forward. Again you can see that the variable "
"<userinput>$name</userinput>, treated just like a string."
msgstr ""
"Še en primer: <screen>\n"
"$name = ask \"Kako ti je ime?\"\n"
"print \"Živjo \" + $name + \"! Vso srečo pri učenju umetnosti "
"programiranja...\"\n"
"</screen> Precej naravnost. Spet lahko vidite, da je spremenljivka "
"<userinput>$name</userinput> obravnavana kot niz."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:538
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using variables the <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</link> is "
"very helpful. It shows you the contents of all variables that are currently "
"in use."
msgstr ""
"Pri uporabi spremenljivk je <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inšpektor</link> "
"zelo koristen. Prikazuje vsebino vseh spremenljivk, ki so trenutno v uporabi."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:544
#, no-c-format
msgid "Controlling execution"
msgstr "Nadzor izvajanja"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The execution controllers enable you &mdash; as their name implies &mdash; "
"to control execution."
msgstr ""
"Krmilniki izvajanja vam omogočajo &mdash; kot pove njihovo ime &mdash; za "
"nadzor izvajanja."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:546
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Execution controlling commands are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with "
"dark green in a bold font type. The brackets are mostly used together with "
"execution controllers and they are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with "
"black."
msgstr ""
"Ukazi za nadzor izvajanja so <glossterm>poudarjeni</glossterm> s temno "
"zeleno v krepki pisavi. Oklepaji se večinoma uporabljajo skupaj z "
"izvajalnimi krmilniki in so <glossterm>poudarjeni</glossterm> s črno."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:549
#, no-c-format
msgid "Have the turtle wait"
msgstr "Želva naj počaka"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have done some programming in &kturtle; you have might noticed that "
"the turtle can be very quick at drawing. This command makes the turtle wait "
"for a given amount of time."
msgstr ""
"Če ste že nekaj programirali v &kturtle; morda ste opazili, da zna želva "
"zelo hitro risati. Ta ukaz poskrbi, da želva čaka določen čas."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>wait</term>"
msgstr "<term>wait</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>wait</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>wait</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid "wait X"
msgstr "wait X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>wait</userinput> makes the turtle wait for X seconds. <screen>\n"
"repeat 36 {\n"
"  forward 5\n"
"  turnright 10\n"
"  wait 0.5\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> This code draws a circle, but the turtle will wait half a second "
"after each step. This gives the impression of a slow-moving turtle."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>wait</userinput> poskrbi, da želva čaka X sekund. <screen>\n"
"ponovi 36 {\n"
"   naprej 5\n"
"   zavijanje desno 10\n"
"   počakaj 0,5\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Ta koda nariše krog, vendar bo želva po vsakem koraku čakala pol "
"sekunde. To daje vtis počasne želve."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Execute <quote>if</quote>"
msgstr "Izvedi <quote>if</quote>"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>if</term>"
msgstr "<term>if</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>if</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>if</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:568
#, no-c-format
msgid "if <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... }"
msgstr "if <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... }"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:568
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The code that is placed between the brackets will only be executed "
"<userinput>if</userinput> the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean value</"
"link> evaluates <quote>true</quote>. <screen>\n"
"$x = 6\n"
"if $x &gt; 5 {\n"
"  print \"$x is greater than five!\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> On the first line <userinput>$x</userinput> is set to 6. On the "
"second line a <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparing operator</"
"link> is used to evaluate <userinput>$x &gt; 5</userinput>. Since this "
"evaluates <quote>true</quote>, 6 is larger than 5, the execution controller "
"<userinput>if</userinput> will allow the code between the brackets to be "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"Koda, ki je v oklepaju, bo izvedena samo, <userinput>če</userinput> <link "
"linkend=\"boolean-value\">logična vrednost</link> ovrednoti <quote>true</"
"quote>. <screen>\n"
"$x = 6\n"
"if $x &gt; 5 {\n"
"  print \"$x is greater than five!\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> V prvi vrstici je <userinput>$x</userinput> nastavljen na 6. V "
"drugi vrstici se <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">operator primerjave</"
"link> uporablja za ovrednotenje <userinput> $x &gt; 5</userinput>. Ker to "
"ovrednoti <quote>true</quote>, 6 je večje od 5, bo krmilnik izvajanja "
"<userinput>če</userinput> dovolil izvedbo kode med oklepaji."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:577
#, no-c-format
msgid "If not, in other words: <quote>else</quote>"
msgstr "Če ne, z drugimi besedami: <quote>else</quote>"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>else</term>"
msgstr "<term>else</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>else</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>else</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "if <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... } else { ... }"
msgstr "if <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... } else { ... }"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>else</userinput> can be used in addition to the execution "
"controller <link linkend=\"if\"><userinput>if</userinput></link>. The code "
"between the brackets after <userinput>else</userinput> is only executed if "
"the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> evaluates <quote>false</"
"quote>. <screen>\n"
"reset\n"
"$x = 4\n"
"if $x &gt; 5 {\n"
"  print \"$x is greater than five!\"\n"
"} else {\n"
"  print \"$x is smaller than six!\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> The <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparing operator</"
"link> evaluates the expression <userinput>$x &gt; 5</userinput>. Since 4 is "
"not greater than 5 the expression evaluates <quote>false</quote>. This means "
"the code between the brackets after <userinput>else</userinput> gets "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>else</userinput> je mogoče uporabiti poleg krmilnika izvajanja "
"<link linkend=\"if\"><userinput>if</userinput></link>. Koda med oklepaji za "
"<userinput>else</userinput> se izvede le, če <link linkend=\"boolean-value"
"\">boolean</link> oceni <quote>false</quote>. <screen>\n"
"ponastavi\n"
"$x = 4\n"
"if $x &gt; 5 {\n"
"  print \"$x is greater than five!\"\n"
"} else {\n"
"  print \"$x is smaller than six!\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">operator primerjanja</link> "
"ovrednoti izraz <userinput>$x &gt; 5</userinput>. Ker 4 ni večje od 5, izraz "
"oceni <quote>false</quote>. To pomeni, da se koda med oklepaji po "
"<userinput>else</userinput> izvede."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>while</quote> loop"
msgstr "Zanka <quote>while</quote>"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>while</term>"
msgstr "<term>while</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>while</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>while</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid "while <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... }"
msgstr "while <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... }"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The execution controller <userinput>while</userinput> is a lot like <link "
"linkend=\"if\"><userinput>if</userinput></link>. The difference is that "
"<userinput>while</userinput> keeps repeating (looping) the code between the "
"brackets until the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> evaluates "
"<quote>false</quote>. <screen>\n"
"$x = 1\n"
"while $x &lt; 5 {\n"
"  forward 10\n"
"  wait 1\n"
"  $x = $x + 1\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> On the first line <userinput>$x</userinput> is set to 1. On the "
"second line <userinput>$x &lt; 5</userinput> is evaluated. Since the answer "
"to this question is <quote>true</quote> the execution controller "
"<userinput>while</userinput> starts executing the code between the brackets "
"until the <userinput>$x &lt; 5</userinput> evaluates <quote>false</quote>. "
"In this case the code between the brackets will be executed 4 times, because "
"every time the fifth line is executed <userinput>$x</userinput> increases by "
"1."
msgstr ""
"Krmilnik izvajanja <userinput>while</userinput> je zelo podoben <link "
"linkend=\"if\"><userinput>if</userinput></link>. Razlika je v tem, da "
"<userinput>medtem ko</userinput> ponavlja (zanka) kodo med oklepaji, dokler "
"<link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> ne oceni <quote>false</"
"quote>. <screen>\n"
"$x = 1\n"
"while $x &lt; 5 {\n"
"  forward 10\n"
"  wait 1\n"
"  $x = $x + 1\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> V prvi vrstici je <userinput>$x</userinput> nastavljen na 1. V "
"drugi vrstici <userinput>$x &lt; 5</userinput> je ocenjeno. Ker je odgovor "
"na to vprašanje <quote>true</quote>, izvajalni krmilnik <userinput>medtem "
"ko</userinput> začne izvajati kodo med oklepaji, dokler se <userinput>$x "
"&lt; 5</userinput> oceni <quote>false</quote>. V tem primeru bo koda med "
"oklepaji izvedena 4-krat, ker se vsakič, ko se izvede peta vrstica, "
"<userinput>$x</userinput> poveča za 1."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>repeat</quote> loop"
msgstr "Zanka <quote>repeat</quote>"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>repeat</term>"
msgstr "<term>repeat</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>repeat</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>repeat</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:607
#, no-c-format
msgid "repeat <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> { ... }"
msgstr "repeat <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> { ... }"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The execution controller <userinput>repeat</userinput> is a lot like <link "
"linkend=\"while\"><userinput>while</userinput></link>. The difference is "
"that <userinput>repeat</userinput> keeps repeating (looping) the code "
"between the brackets for as many times as the given number."
msgstr ""
"Krmilnik izvajanja <userinput>repeat</userinput> je zelo podoben <link "
"linkend=\"while\"><userinput>while</userinput></link>. Razlika je v tem, da "
"<userinput>repeat</userinput> ponavlja (zanka) kodo med oklepaji tolikokrat, "
"kot je podano število."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>for</quote> loop, a counting loop"
msgstr "Zanka <quote>for</quote>, zanka štetja"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>for</term>"
msgstr "<term>for</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>for</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>for</primary>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>to</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>to</primary>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "step"
msgstr "step"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"for <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> = <link "
"linkend=\"number\">number</link> to <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> "
"{ ... }"
msgstr ""
"for <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> = <link "
"linkend=\"number\">number</link> to <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> "
"{ ... }"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>for</userinput> loop is a <quote>counting loop</quote>, &ie; "
"it keeps count for you. The first number sets the variable to the value in "
"the first loop. Every loop the number is increased until the second number "
"is reached. <screen>\n"
"for $x = 1 to 10 {\n"
"  print $x * 7\n"
"  forward 15\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Every time the code between the brackets is executed the "
"<userinput>$x</userinput> is increased by 1, until <userinput>$x</userinput> "
"reaches the value of 10. The code between the brackets prints the <userinput>"
"$x</userinput> multiplied by 7. After this program finishes its execution "
"you will see the times table of 7 on the canvas."
msgstr ""
"Zanka <userinput>for</userinput> je <quote>zanka štetja</quote>, &ie; šteje "
"za vas. Prvo število nastavi spremenljivko na vrednost v prvi zanki. Vsako "
"zanko se število povečuje, dokler ni doseženo drugo število. <screen>\n"
"for $x = 1 to 10 {\n"
"  print $x * 7\n"
"  forward 15\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Vsakič, ko se izvede koda med oklepaji, se <userinput>$x</"
"userinput> poveča za 1, dokler <userinput>$x</userinput> ne doseže vrednosti "
"10. Koda med oklepaji se natisne <userinput>$x</userinput> pomnoženo s 7. Ko "
"ta program konča z izvajanjem, boste na platnu videli časovno tabelo 7."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "The default step size of a loop is 1, you can use an other value with"
msgstr "Privzeta velikost koraka zanke je 1, lahko uporabite drugo vrednost"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"for <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> = <link "
"linkend=\"number\">number</link> to <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> "
"step <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> { ... }"
msgstr ""
"for <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> = <link "
"linkend=\"number\">number</link> to <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> "
"step <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> { ... }"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Leave a loop"
msgstr "Zapusti zanko"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>break</term>"
msgstr "<term>break</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>break</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>break</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:635
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>break</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>break</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:635
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Terminates the current loop immediately and transfers control to the "
"statement immediately following that loop."
msgstr ""
"Takoj prekine trenutno zanko in prenese nadzor na stavek, ki sledi tej zanki."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:642
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stop executing your program"
msgstr "Prenehaj z izvajanjem svojega programa"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:645
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>exit</term>"
msgstr "<term>exit</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:645
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>exit</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>exit</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>exit</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>exit</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finishes the execution of your program."
msgstr "Konča izvajanje vašega programa."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:653
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checking assertions at runtime"
msgstr "Preverjanje trditev med izvajanjem"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>assert</term>"
msgstr "<term>assert</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>assert</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>assert</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "assert <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link>"
msgstr "assert <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can be used to reason about program or input correctness."
msgstr "Lahko se uporablja za razmišljanje o pravilnosti programa ali vnosa."

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$in = ask \"What is your year of birth?\"\n"
"# the year must be positive\n"
"assert $in > 0"
msgstr ""
"$in = ask \"Katero je tvoje leto rojstva?\"\n"
"# leto mora biti pozitivno\n"
"assert $in > 0"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:668
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create your own commands with <quote>learn</quote>"
msgstr "Ustvarite lastne ukaze z <quote>learn</quote>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:669
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>learn</userinput><indexterm><primary>learn</primary></indexterm> "
"is special as it is used to create your own commands. The commands you "
"create can take <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</glossterm> and "
"return <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">output</glossterm>. Let us take a "
"look at how a new command is created: <screen>\n"
"learn circle $x {\n"
"  repeat 36 {\n"
"    forward $x\n"
"    turnleft 10\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> The new command is called <userinput>circle</userinput>. "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> takes one <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">input</glossterm> argument, to set the size of the circle. "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> returns no <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">output</glossterm>. The <userinput>circle</userinput> command can now be "
"used like a normal command in the rest of the code. See this example:"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>learn</userinput><indexterm><primary>learn</primary></indexterm> "
"je poseben, saj se uporablja za ustvarjanje lastnih ukazov. Ukazi, ki jih "
"ustvarite, lahko sprejmejo <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</"
"glossterm> in vrnejo <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">output</glossterm>. "
"Oglejmo si, kako se ustvari nov ukaz: <screen>\n"
"learn circle $x {\n"
"   repeat 36 {\n"
"     forward $x\n"
"     turnleft 10\n"
"   }\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Nov ukaz se imenuje <userinput>circle</userinput>. "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> sprejme en <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">input</glossterm> argument za nastavitev velikosti kroga. "
"<userinput>krog</userinput> ne vrne nobenega <glossterm linkend=\"input-"
"output\">output</glossterm>. Ukaz <userinput>circle</userinput> je zdaj "
"mogoče uporabiti kot običajni ukaz v preostali kodi. Glejte ta primer:"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:672
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"learn circle $X {\n"
"  repeat 36 {\n"
"    forward $X \n"
"    turnleft 10 \n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"go 200,200 \n"
"circle 20\n"
"\n"
"go 300,200 \n"
"circle 40"
msgstr ""
"learn circle $X {\n"
"  repeat 36 {\n"
"    forward $X \n"
"    turnleft 10 \n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"go 200,200 \n"
"circle 20\n"
"\n"
"go 300,200 \n"
"circle 40"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the next example, a command with a return<indexterm><primary>return</"
"primary></indexterm> value is created. <screen>\n"
"learn faculty $x {\n"
"  $r = 1\n"
"  for $i = 1 to $x {\n"
"    $r = $r * $i\n"
"  }\n"
"  return $r\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"print faculty 5\n"
"</screen> In this example a new command called <userinput>faculty</"
"userinput> is created. If the input of this command is <userinput>5</"
"userinput> then the output is <userinput>5*4*3*2*1</userinput>. By using "
"<userinput>return</userinput> the <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">output</glossterm> value is specified and the execution is returned."
msgstr ""
"V naslednjem primeru je ustvarjen ukaz z vrednostjo "
"return<indexterm><primary>return</primary></indexterm>. <screen>\n"
"learn faculty $x {\n"
"  $r = 1\n"
"  for $i = 1 to $x {\n"
"    $r = $r * $i\n"
"  }\n"
"  return $r\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"print faculty 5\n"
"</screen> V tem primeru je ustvarjen nov ukaz z imenom <userinput>faculty</"
"userinput>. Če je vnos tega ukaza <userinput>5</userinput>, potem je izhod "
"<userinput>5*4*3*2*1</userinput>. Z uporabo <userinput>return</userinput> je "
"določena <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">izhodna</glossterm> vrednost in "
"vrnjena je izvedba."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Commands can have more than one <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</"
"glossterm>. In the next example, a command that draws a rectangle is "
"created: <screen>\n"
"learn box $x, $y {\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Now you can run <userinput>box 50, 100</userinput> and the turtle "
"will draw a rectangle on the canvas."
msgstr ""
"Ukazi imajo lahko več kot en <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">vnos</"
"glossterm>. V naslednjem primeru je ustvarjen ukaz, ki nariše pravokotnik: "
"<screen>\n"
"learn box $x, $y {\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Zdaj lahko zaženete <userinput>box 50, 100</userinput> in želva bo "
"narisala pravokotnik na platno."
